<h1>Ryan Barrington Cox</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://trailofsparks.org/now/">trailofsparks.org/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Asheville
NC
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Musician, Storyteller, Software Developer/Tester with NOAA <<a href="http://www.noaa.gov/>">http://www.noaa.gov/></a>
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I make, break and enjoy as much as possible.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
My life is a quest for creative flow.  Music was my vessel for two decades. Nowadays I'm finding flow in technology, communication and family.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Be present.  Fail as much as you can.  Reflect.  Meaningful work is rare and valuable.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Secrets of a Buccaneer-Scholar by James Marcus Bach
</p>

